[SN]TITLE[SN]
Fire at St Christopher's School, Wrexham, 'accidental'

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A fire which broke out a special school in Wrexham is believed to have been caused by a light fitting overheating.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Four appliances from Wrexham, Chirk and Llangollen were called to St Christopher's School in Hightown, at 02:10 BST on Saturday.
North Wales Fire and Rescue Service said the cause was under investigation but it is thought to be accidental.
The firefighters said the roof of the school was "well alight" when they arrived.
The school provides education for children with special educational needs, with about 280 pupils.
